Task 1 – Read Inventory

Open inventory.json using with open().

Use json.load() to convert JSON data into a Python list.

Print the number of books using len(inventory).

Task 2 – Update and Save

Create a dictionary for the new book.

Append it to the list using inventory.append(new_book).

Save the updated list back to the file using json.dump() with indent=4.

Task 3 – Display Inventory

Read the file again.

Loop through each book using a for loop.

Print the book details in the required format.